Rating: 4
My mom and I love this recipe! Usually we make a raspberry crush and serve w/berries. SO PRETTY! We also put plastic wrap in muffin tins or ramekins to help get panna cotta out. Admittedly, you get some wrinkles in the panna cotta - but usually not an issue. This is a light and delicious dessert.

Rating: 3
I had guests for dinner and made this. It came perfect, despite the fact that a lot of the gelatin seemed to strain out. I served it with gold and green kiwifruit and feijoas. Personally I found the fruit too tart and acid to match the tart panna cotta, but my guests and extremely fussy husband all loved it.

